                  <persName id="t18271025-254-person1315">
                  MARY 
                  THOMPSON
               <interp inst="t18271025-254-person1315" type="surname" value="THOMPSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271025-254-person1315" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18271025-254-person1315" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am wife of Thomas Thompson. I sell vegetables in Spitalfields-market - last Saturday a person brought these things to me from the wash - I put them into my basket, and at half-past eleven o'clock, when I packed up, the prisoner came to help me home with my vegetables - he <rs id="t18271025-254-deflabel1453" type="occupation">works in the market</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271025-254-defend1313 t18271025-254-deflabel1453"></join> - he helped me with my things into the cellar, and I found the basket had been opened, and the bundle gone - he came next morning to take away my cart - I called him aside, and told him of it- he denied it - I asked where he lived - he said no where - he would not tell me where they were - I called the officer, and when he saw his staff he said the things were at his mother's.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271025-254-person1316">
